wiki.text:
'Forenoon' is the part of the day between sunrise and
noon.<ref>http://www.thefreedictionary.com/forenoon</ref>

The term should not be confused with "fore noon" (two separate words), which is
a translation of the Latin ante meridiem (a.m.), meaning a time between 12:00
midnight and 12:00 midday.
